# Code owners for this repository.
#
# The last matching pattern wins, so this single rule makes @ericfisherdev the
# owner of everything. Add narrower rules BELOW this line, not above it.
#
# What this does today: GitHub automatically requests a review from the owner on
# every pull request they did not open themselves -- Dependabot's, and anyone
# else's once there is a second contributor.
#
# What it deliberately does NOT do: gate merges. Branch protection leaves
# require_code_owner_reviews off, because GitHub does not let anyone approve
# their own pull request. With a sole owner who is also the sole author, turning
# it on would add a requirement nobody present can satisfy. Revisit that when a
# second person can approve.

* @ericfisherdev
